<subSubSection pageId="253" pageNumber="858" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="253.[789,1383,1358,1782]" lastBlockId="253.[170,1381,1787,3473]" pageId="253" pageNumber="858">
<taxonomicName box="[791,913,1512,1546]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Maxomys</taxonomicName>
is sister to all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1230,1324,1512,1546]" pageId="253" pageNumber="883" rank="tribe" tribe="Rattini">Rattini</taxonomicName>
ex- cept 
<taxonomicName box="[874,1003,1556,1585]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Crunomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Crunomys</taxonomicName>
, which is nested within 
<taxonomicName box="[791,913,1591,1625]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Maxomys</taxonomicName>
phylogenetically, making the genus paraphyletic. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1050,1268,1634,1663]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surifer">Maxomys surifer</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[832,986,1670,1704]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bartelsii">M. bartelsii</taxonomicName>
, and this clade is sister to all other 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1053,1713,1742]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Maxomys</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Robinson &amp; Kloss" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1178,1278,1713,1742]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moi">M. moi</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surifer">Maxomys surifer</taxonomicName>
almost certainly represents a species complex, with considerable genetic and morphological variation throughout its distribution. It has been included as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1028,1146,1826,1860]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="253" pageNumber="858" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rajah">M. rajah</taxonomicName>
in the past, but morphological and genetic data support its recognition as a distinct species. Seven subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
